That Archilochian metre which from its predominance (and that of others similar) gave in an early century its own ap- pellation to the whole book of Epodes, is not at this day much better understood from Gaisford's Hephaestio, (1810,) pp. 129. 368. or from Hermann's Elementa Doctrinae Metricae, (1816,) L, iii. c. xv. than it might have been known for any practical purpose in the year 1578.
